{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":221479,"duration_api_ms":198244,"num_turns":42,"result":"The fix is complete. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Problem\n\nThe codebase had an import error when running tests due to a Python 3.12 compatibility issue in `dask/utils.py`. When the `derived_from` decorator is applied to accessor functions in `dask/dataframe/accessor.py`, it sets `func.__wrapped__` to a pandas property object. Later, when `inspect.signature()` is called on the function, Python 3.12 follows the `__wrapped__` chain and raises a `TypeError` (not `ValueError`) when it encounters the non-callable property object.\n\n## Fix\n\nIn `dask/utils.py`, line 936, the exception handler only caught `ValueError`. The fix changes it to catch both `ValueError` and `TypeError`:\n\n```python\n# Before\nexcept ValueError:\n    not_supported = []\n\n# After  \nexcept (ValueError, TypeError):\n    not_supported = []\n```\n\nThis minimal one-line change allows the import to succeed and all 445+ tests in `test_array_core.py` to pass.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"7a0705cb-dcb0-4078-9d02-03b392a50078","total_cost_usd":9.492592350000004,"usage":{"input_tokens":3010147,"cache_creation_input_tokens":68693,"cache_read_input_tokens":155992,"output_tokens":10517,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"cache_deleted_input_tokens":0,"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"MiniMax-M2.5-highspeed":{"inputTokens":3010147,"outputTokens":10517,"cacheReadInputTokens":155992,"cacheCreationInputTokens":68693,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":9.492592350000004,"contextWindow":196000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"98291dd5-0c58-4c7b-af73-b592a0a14420"}
